  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They had no idea about my mother, and of course, I didn't, either, and I wrote this to him in the letter.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And this is an uncle who came home with his wife and daughter, who is just 20 days younger than I am.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when they came home to what was Czechoslovakia at the time, we set up the monument for my grandpa, my uncle's father, in the cemetery, because he died when I was six months old.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we dedicated the monument in the cemetery, and that picture I found in an American relative's album, which I will submit to you today for-- for this.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't know that the war was finished until I got to Sweden.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When we reached-- I remember that, in Copenhagen, I still saw German soldiers, with guns on their shoulders, walking back and forth at the train station because the war was still on, it was just the tail end.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was five days before the war ended when I was liberated, you see.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But then, remember, maybe some of the other women knew, but I was in very bad shape and I was probably preoccupied with my well-being or with my problems, rather.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I asked the Swedish family to help me locate my family.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I started writing to the Czech address, the same place we had our house-- we had a seven-room house and a big barn.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] The-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] yes, to the Czech address, Hungarian address, and eventually, I had a letter, months and months after I was liberated, that my mother received six letters from me at the same time, written by me over a period of time.",
      "word_count": 49
    }
  ],
